<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="a" from="1" to="3" step="1"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="b" from="1" to="3" step="1" exclude="$a"/>
  
  <function name="f" variable="y" symbolic="false"> -1*(y+$a)*(y-$b)</function>
  <function name="g" variable="y" symbolic="false"> pi*(y+$a)^2*(y-$b)^2</function>
  <function name="g1" variable="y" symbolic="false"> pi*((y+$a)*(y-$b))^2</function>
  <function name="g2" variable="y" symbolic="false"> pi*$f^2</function>
  <function name="F"> pi*( 1/3*x^3*($a^2 - 4*$a*$b + $b^2) + $a^2*$b^2*x + 1/2*x^4*($a - $b) + $a*$b*x^2*($b - $a) + x^5/5 ) </function>
  
  <math name="intValue" simplify>$$F($b)-$$F(-$a)</math>

</setup>  

  <p>
    Consider the curve defined by <m>x = $f</m> and the finite region, <m>\mathcal{R}</m>, that its graph bounds along with the <m>y</m>-axis.
  </p>

  <p> 
    <ol marker="a.">
      <li>
        <p>
          Sketch a graph of the region, <m>\mathcal{R}</m>, and then sketch the solid generated by revoloving this region about the <m>y</m>-axis.  
        </p>  
        <p>
          Find an integral expression that represents the volume of the resulting solid of revolution.  Do so by filling in the blanks below; once you identify the lower and upper limits of integration, those numbers will appear in the integral expression below.
        </p>

        <p>
          lower limit of integration: <m>a = </m> <answer name="lower">-$a</answer>
        </p>
        <p>
          upper limit of integration: <m>b = </m> <answer name="upper">$b</answer>
        </p>

        <p>
          Integral expression for the volume, <m>V</m>, of the solid of revolution: 
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>V = \displaystyle\int_{$lower}^{$upper}</m><mathInput name="int1" minWidth="100" /><m>d</m><mathInput name="dWhat" minWidth="15"/><answer><award><when>($int1 = $g or $int1 = $g2) and $dWhat = y </when></award></answer>
        </p> 
        
          <!-- testing -->  
         <p> <m>int1 = $int1</m>, <m>$g</m> , <m>$g1</m> , <m>$g2</m> , $dWhat, </p> 
          <!-- testing -->
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Evaluate the integral to find the numerical value of the volume, <m>V</m>, and report the value below.  Report your result to an accuracy within <m>0.0001</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>V = </m><mathInput name="intVal" minWidth="40" /> <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.0001" allowedErrorIsAbsolute><award><when>$intValue=$intVal </when></award></answer>
          <!-- , $$F($b), $$F(-$a), $$F($b)-$$F(-$a), <m>F(x) = $F</m> -->
        </p>  
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>